But the ad (was that an ad?) at the end, sheesh!  NSFW

@Chris 

"Sri" comes from Sanskrit, so you run into it all over Southeast Asia, in various forms and uses. It's where the name of Sri Lanka comes from, though I think it just means "resplendent" in Sinhalese (as it did in Sanskrit), and isn't used as an honorific.
I thought it was a nice clue, though of course you don't know whether to enter SRI or SIR until you get a cross in the right place.

